text.section:
Persons that lease space at a marine facility from the Maryland Port Administration shall implement a program that:
Prohibits the sale, purchase, transfer, use, or possession of alcohol or drugs at a port facility;
Provides a plan that includes the nondiscriminatory administration of tests for the presence of alcohol or drugs in accordance with established testing procedures, including random, reasonable cause, post accident, and return-to-work, or post treatment testing of safety-sensitive employees, and pre-employment test for the presence of drugs, of employees;
Provides for rehabilitation programs and disciplinary and sanction procedures for individuals who violate the Program;
Provides sufficient notice to employees of testing procedures, consent, and other requirements of the Program;
Provides adequate security measures for collection, chain of custody, and handling of test material; and
Establishes procedures for the reporting, review, and appeal of test results.
